Title: Bratz - Rock Angelz

reviewText: I don't get how you thought this animation was so cheep it probably took a month to make. But I know you know that isbn't true. Cause think of it, look at their hair, their hair was moving like it was real, and not to mentioned they changed their hairstyle a dozen times, 4 different ones for each girl. And their make-up, they changed their make-up too, a lot of times, and their outfits, they came up with a lot of styles for them that would take forever to make, and their accessories, which their earrings moved around a lot too. And also, they had to make other people there, like other girls, boys, and not to mention make their outfits, and do the girls make-up, and do their hairstyles. And also, all the places they went, like London, they had to make a lot of places for that, and Pinz, that punk club they went to, and the mall, and their office, tons of places. And also, they had to write songs for the movie, they wrote 10 songs for the movie, so that took a lot of work for the people who sing it. And also, getting the people to do their voices, they had a lot of people, and they had Tia Morway, and other people that did voices for characters, did you know the person that did Roxxi and Fianna (on one of their Tv shows) is the same person that did Maggie from "the Buzz on Maggie", and the person that did Yasmin is the same person that did Yasmin is the same person that did Trixie from "The Fairly Oddparents" and Kimi from "Rugrats" and "All Grown Up", and the person that does Jade is the same person that did Zoe from "the Proud Family". Which probably took a lot of work as well. So, this proves that MGAE worked their butt off to make this movie, a ton of work, and they did a great job, I know people didn't hate it, but they want too cause they don't like Bratz, and you probably don't like them cause their almost better then Barbie now, I don't like My Scene dolls anymore, but their movie is nice, and also, some people never even saw it, and they say they saw it and say it's bad so people won't buy it, but it doesn't work, these reveiws need to be for actual Bratz fans. Like me. And also, most of these reveiws are worthless, cause wayyyyyy before this movie came out, people were giving it bad reveiws, well, hello, their movie wasn't out yet, they also said they copied My Scene doll cause the My Scene dolls boys were in a band in their movie, but that was in the movie, and I knwo MGAE wouldn't watch their movies, so they wouldn't know, and also, they said MGAE copied Barbie, well, that is not true, you see, MGAE first Brazt movie didn't sell that well, cause it wasn't that terribly good, so they figured if they made it CGI animation, then it would sell better, and it did, a lot better, not to mention they have their own TV show too, and magazine. So, Brazt fans, this movie was great, and don't let Bratz haters tell you that, cause, well, they hate Bratz, so why should we trust you? This movie was great, and the animation was awsome too, so don't listen to bashers. Bratz rock.
summary: This movie rocked, smae with the animation
Title: Bratz - Rock Angelz

reviewText: Send your Barbie videos to Grandma, 'cuz the BRATZ rule DVD for today's generation!  These passion-for-fashion gurlz on on the cutting-edge of hip and cool, always leading the way (instead of desperately scrambling to follow trends like "My Scene" and "Barbie").  Rock Angelz is a huge step-forward in animation quality (from the prior "Starrin' & Stylin" which looked pretty lame by today's animation standards).  Word is that the NEW BRATZ video is LIGHT YEARS ahead of even "ROCK ANGELZ," and that "Livin It Up With The Bratz" will be available on DVD Feb. 14, 2006.  Watch out Barbie... time to go to the Malibu Retirement Home!!
summary: Better than Barbie videos by LIGHT YEARS!!!

reviewText: Having trawled through 200+ reviews on this film, I've come to the conclusion that Bratz obviously retards the intelligence of those that collect them. At least 40% of the reviews on here are repeats, 5% seem to be about the movie and the rest is Bratz and My Scene fans calling each other names, with the Bratz fans making the dumbest statements.Face it, you whinge about Barbie being a bad example for the young, but honestly the Bratz tagline is 'girls with a passion for fashion and boys' So the only important things in life are clothes and dating, hey if that ain't sexism what is? At least barbie (not my scene) got to be a doctor.
